en_225415_0	The strike launched by several trade unions including railway drivers and regulators regarding salary anomalies continues today for the 7 th day.
en_225415_1	The Railway Control Room stated that seven trains were added to the train schedule this morning.
en_225415_2	Meanwhile, the Co-convener of the Railway Monitoring Operations Officers' Association Lal Ariyaratne stated that their trade unions will meet today at 10.00 am to discuss measures to include all the railway trade unions for the continuous strike.
en_225415_3	At a Cabinet meeting held yesterday, a proposal to make the railway service a closed service in order to solve railway employees' problems was approved.
